# Personal site UI

Preserve the minimal one-pager: system fonts, light/dark tokens (`--bg`, `--fg`, `--muted`, `--border`, `--accent`, `--accent-fg`), centered `main` max-width `38rem`.

## Do

- Extract reusable UI into `src/components/` once a section has real structure (gallery, cards)
- Full-bleed sections: `width: 100vw; margin-left/right: calc(50% - 50vw)` — do **not** add `max-width: 100%` (it kills breakout)
- Prefer `overflow-x: clip` on `html`/`body` if a full-bleed scroller would otherwise widen the page
- Match existing density and tone (short timeline lines, muted secondary text)

## Don’t

- Don’t add Tailwind or a new design system unless asked
- Don’t use purple/glow/AI-slop defaults; accent is orange
- Don’t put cards in the hero or turn the page into a dashboard
- Don’t invent separate detail routes for content that should stay homepage-only

## Responsive scrollers

One fluid formula from phone to desktop (peek of next item). Avoid `min-width` media queries that replace fluid sizing with a fixed px width — that breaks mid-size viewports and feels “broken” on mobile.
